title: FOIA - North Carolina State Highway Patrol - Emails on viral twitter video of officer

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any internal emails sent and/or received from any staff member from 2/16/2023 to 2/17/2023 containing/mentioning "twitter".

Any responsive documents should include all email headers, the full body of the email, and full copies of any attachments for each email.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

J Ader

title: Melissa Jane Weiss, Privacy Act Request Under 5 U.S.C. 552a

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a request for information under the Privacy Act , 5 U.S.C. § 552a.

This Request seeks access to: a) any and all records and/or documents that have been prepared, received, transmitted, collected and/or maintained by the FBI, USDOJ, or DHS concerning me or my activities; b) The Terrorist Screening Database (TSDB) list; and c) the list containing all the agencies, entities, private corporations or individuals with whom you have shared the TSDB; and d) provide a copy of the Standard Nomination Form or original information that was used to place my name on the TSDB.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Melissa Jane Weiss
